rComments: She is very personable and friendly. She was always available for comments/questions/concerns after class, in office hours and through e-mail. That being said, she is a tougher marker than other professors such as Daneisi. I received an overall grade of 82 in her class when I felt I deserved ~85. Readings and lectures were easy to keep up with.
Her lectures are really interesting and involves a lot of discussion. She's really nice and approachable as well. Readings are necessary since she uses them to start discussions in class.
